{"id":6653,"date":"2012-09-19T10:46:55","date_gmt":"2012-09-19T14:46:55","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=6653"},"modified":"2019-04-27T18:46:43","modified_gmt":"2019-04-27T14:46:43","slug":"justice-equal-punishments","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/19\/justice-equal-punishments\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Justice: Legal punishments apply equally in society"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Aisha reported: The Quraysh had been anxious about a woman who had committed theft and they said, \u201cWho will speak to the Messenger of Allah about her?\u201d Some said, \u201cWho would dare to but Usama, one beloved by the Messenger of Allah?\u201d Thus, Usama spoke to him and the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Do you intercede regarding a punishment prescribed by Allah<\/strong>?\u201d The Prophet then stood up and addressed the people, saying, \u201c<strong>O people, those who came before you were destroyed because if a person of high status committed theft among them, they would spare him, but if a person of lower status committed theft, they would apply the punishment upon him. By Allah, if Fatima the daughter of Muhammad were to steal, I would have cut off her hand<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1688<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0642\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0634\u064b\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0634\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0632\u064f\u0648\u0645\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u064e\u0651\u062a\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u06